to use a higher starch potato for mashing. The Russet, Desiree or Coliban varieties work well in this recipe.","Potatoes must be completely cooked and soft before mashing. Please refer to <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i> for tips on mashing potatoes.","Serve as a side with any dish, such as the <i>Pork in creamy Marsala wine sauce<\/i> or <i>Beef \"Burgundy\"<\/i> (please refer to the recipes on this recipe chip)."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","40m","4 portions"]}